content.$t:
http://www.meetup.com/The-Ukulele-Assemble/events/142980302/

Hosted by Luther

The Ukulele Assemble is 1 year old! It's been an awesome journey and experience so far, do join us at the sessions if you haven't! 

RSVP Guidelines 
Do RSVP due to limited space at the venue. RSVP will start on 4 October 2013 (Friday), 9.00am onwards and base on first-come-first-serve.

For those who have RSVPed, a gentle reminder to release your slot in advance if you can't make it, so other fellow members can benefit from the experience.

Music Facilitators 
We have a group of Music Facilitators lined up to share their love and interest with the ukulele with everyone. For the month of October, we have Paul L. Amazona to share one of his favourite song with us. :)

Chord Sheets Chord sheets for the session will be uploaded nearing to the date. Do print it out for your reference at: http://www.meetup.com/The-Ukulele-Assemble/files/

Others 
Photo taking is welcome at the sessions but please obtain permission from the group before you do as we have some shy members among us. :)

title.$t: Self-organized hackathon to generate ideas on how to attempt to commercialize AI technology

content.$t:
https://an-evening-with-stefano-virgilli.eventbrite.com/

Host: Luther 

The Sypnosis for the talks are -
Foundation of typography - 45 minutes
Font Face addict Stefano Virgilli will run through an overview of History, Art and Technical specification of Western typography. Don't miss this session if you are into logo design and publishing!


Why after 15 years it's time for me to say Goodbye Adobe - 20 minutes
Stefano Virgilli, perhaps the most certified Adobe Trainer in the world, has planned to retire from training Adobe software to the public. He has a number of reasons within and without Adobe that will be sharing in an unstructured session, open to any type of questions from the public. Don't miss it if you are planning now to jump onto Adobe software.


Singapore to Oman, one way ticket (i.e. Rebooting my life away from Singapore) - 20 minutes
After 6 years spent living and working in Singapore, Stefano Virgilli, married to a Singaporean wife and father of 2 Singaporean children, has moved business and family to Middle East, in emerging Oman. Learn from Stefano advantages and disadvantages of relocating in a developing country vs a fully developed environment.
